narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: CHNS 140 is rigorous, but if you're serious about attaining fluency in Chinese, absolutely pursue Chinese all the way through at Yale.

This class is a lot of work but you will learn so much in just L3 and L4. I will say that the oral exams are weakly structured because it requires so much memorization of the text rather than using your skills in Chinese to carry out a conversation.
